-- в”Ђв”Ђ Cosmic в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Cosmic is an AI-powered headless content management system built for developers and content teams that want a flexible content API paired with built-in AI agents. Founded by Carson Gibbons and Tony Spiro and backed by Y Combinator (W19), Cosmic provides a REST API, TypeScript SDK, CLI, and an MCP server for integrating with AI coding tools like Cursor, Claude Code, and GitHub Copilot.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Tiered monthly subscription with a free forever plan and per-additional-user pricing$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (paid plans start at 49 USD per month)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2014, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$Approximately 8 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$San Francisco, California, United States$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Cosmic Headless CMS Review 2026: Pricing and Features$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Cosmic is an AI-powered headless CMS with a content API, TypeScript SDK, and built-in AI agents. See 2026 pricing, features, pros and cons.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Cosmic is a headless content management system built for teams that want a flexible, API-first content backend combined with built-in artificial intelligence features. The company was started by co-founders Carson Gibbons and Tony Spiro, with the idea for the product taking shape around 2014 and a public launch of an early version around 2016; Cosmic later went through Y Combinator's Winter 2019 (W19) batch, and Tony Spiro serves as CEO. The company is headquartered in San Francisco, California, and, according to available reporting, operates with a small team of roughly eight people, which is typical for a venture-backed, product-led developer tools startup at its stage. As a headless CMS, Cosmic separates content management from content presentation: editors manage structured content, images, and metadata inside a web dashboard, and developers pull that content into any frontend framework or channel, website, mobile app, or other digital product, through a REST API that Cosmic advertises as returning responses in under 100 milliseconds. Developer tooling includes a TypeScript SDK, a command-line interface (CLI), and, reflecting a broader industry shift toward AI-assisted development, a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that plugs directly into AI coding assistants such as Cursor, Claude Code, and GitHub Copilot, letting developers query and modify Cosmic content as part of an AI-assisted coding workflow. Cosmic's most distinctive positioning in 2026 is around AI agents built into the CMS itself, rather than as a bolt-on feature. The company describes several agent types: a Team Agent that lives inside messaging tools such as Slack, WhatsApp, or Telegram, where a user defines its persona and goal and it maintains persistent conversation memory while triggering actions in the CMS, the codebase, or third-party APIs from natural-language instructions; Content Agents that can publish and manage content autonomously; and Code Agents described as able to ship features and fix bugs. On the content-modeling side, Cosmic supports more than 20 metafield types for structuring content, AI-assisted image and video generation for media assets, and a design choice the company markets as no migrations ever, meaning content model changes do not require the kind of database migration scripts common in some other CMS or database-backed systems. Cosmic's content containers are called Buckets, and pricing scales primarily by the number of Buckets, team members, and content Objects included in each plan. The Free plan costs 0 USD per month and includes 1 Bucket, 2 team members, and up to 1,000 Objects, with no credit card required to start. The Builder plan is 49 USD per month and includes 2 Buckets, 3 team members, and up to 5,000 Objects. The Team plan is 299 USD per month and includes 3 Buckets, 5 team members, and up to 20,000 Objects. The Business plan is 499 USD per month and includes 5 Buckets, 10 team members, and up to 50,000 Objects. Across paid plans, additional team members beyond the included allotment can be added for 29 USD per user per month. Cosmic is best suited for development teams building content-driven websites, apps, or SaaS products who want an API-first CMS rather than a traditional monolithic content platform, and particularly for teams interested in experimenting with AI agents that can manage or publish content with minimal manual intervention, or with integrating their CMS content directly into AI-assisted coding tools via the MCP server.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '2440fb35-39af-47b6-a7a4-97190468c891';

